<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-10306] GlobalThread might loop forever</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-10306</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;We did some code refactoring in the `GlobalStateMangerImpl` that can lead to an infinite loop if the global consumer throws an `InvalidOffsetException`. This is a regression bug and thus I marked this ticket as blocker fro 2.6 release.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The issue seem to occur only during the initial bootstrapping of the global store, but not during regular processing.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
